pdtools 0.0.2
  • Reference

Generate a random synthetic pangenome gene presence absence matrix

generate_pangenome.Rd

Generate a random synthetic pangenome gene presence absence matrix

generate_pangenome(
  num_genomes = 100,
  num_genes = 1000,
  core_genome_fraction = 0.75
)

Arguments

num_genomes

number of genomes the matrix will contain
num_genes

number of genes the matrix will contain
core_genome_fraction

fraction of genes that are part of the core genome

Value

gene presence absence matrix (0/1), rows are genomes, columns are genes

Examples

generate_pangenome()
#>            gene_1 gene_2 gene_3 gene_4 gene_5 gene_6 gene_7 gene_8 gene_9
